==============First Push into VSTS-Git using VsCode=============

If you don't have 'Azure Repos' on your machine
    ~ then first Goto Extentions on VsCode IDE and install 'Azure Repos'


1. Open source in VsCode.
2. Commit your changes locally.
3. Open Terminal
  3.1 git remote add <RepoName> <URL of Repo>
  3.2 git config --global user.name "sandhipdhall1996@gmail.com" 
  3.3 git config --global user.email "sandhipdhall1996@gmail.com"
  3.4 git config --global --list
  3.5 git push -u SafaiKaramchariAttendance --all
  3.6 git push -u <RepoName> --all

(after that you are able to commit and push changes in that Repo)

======For Commit and Push
1. Go to Source control
   1.1 Enter Commit message
   1.2 click on options then 'Push' into server
